olor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukalcor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalcor </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/02 4:59:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23012.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What AA skills would you choose?</span><hr size=1> i did crit1, and dura3 for what its worth. <p><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7916>*Kalcor's Stuff!*</a></center><p><center><img src=http://kalcor.homestead.com/files/sig.jpg></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/02 6:27:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23012.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What AA skills would you choose?</span><hr size=1> Haven't gotten there yet, but I plan on Crit one and Finish one, just because I think rogues ought to be able to cut down the enemy as they run... from there we'll see.<br><br>Jarkell Ravensteel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukayleighdrake.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KayleighDrake</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/02 7:07:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23012.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What AA skills would you choose?</span><hr size=1> Choices: <br><br>Crits: they're fun, you get to spam people with nice crit backstabs. Doesn't do tons for your damage, but high fun factor.<br><br>Durability: more hitpoints is good. Not much more you can say than that<br><br>Finishing Blow: eh. I have it. I don't care for it. It doesn't go off much and not on the stuff I really want to finish off. This one should, imho, be way down the list.<br><br>Combat Agility/Stability: taking less damage is good.<br><br>If I were you, I'd take crits, then durability/agility/stability in whatever order you prefer. If you raid a lot, go with durability first. If you don't, try the others. Those three are all good and you'll want them all eventually - it's just a matter of what order.<br><br> <p><hr align="center" size="1"> <center><IMG SRC="http://www.logalt.net/upload/osprey-sig.jpg"><BR> <A HREF = "http://www.silentsentinels.com"; TARGET = "_blank">Silent  Sentinels -- Come See Us</A> <BR>A.K.A. Kayleigh Silverwing, Templar of Tunare</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uviscerspineshank.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Viscer Spineshank</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/02 1:07:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23012.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What AA skills would you choose?</span><hr size=1> So far I have 1 in agility, 2 in crit, 1 in durability.<br><br>If I were to do it again I would have done, 3 in durability then agility, mitigation and then crit......maybe crit before 2's or 3's in agility/mitigation. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4347"><IMG src="http://www.nwlink.com/~bstevens/Rogues/images/viscer1.jpg" border=0></a><br><a href=http://www.casus-belli.net><I>Casus Belli</I></a>-An Occasion for War<BR>Ayonae Ro<BR>"You can run but you'll just die tired"--KAAOS</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utobyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tobyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/02 10:40:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23012.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What AA skills would you choose?</span><hr size=1> The purists answer is simple, only one of the options increases your DPS, max CF.  Thats what I did but given the opportunity Im not sure Id retake that route.  Not saying I wouldnt but I would certainly rethink it.<br><br>Combat stability is simple.  Figure out what your ac is and go from there.  Ac cap for rogues is most likely 1200 or very close to this.  CS will increase that cap by 2, 5, and 10 percent.  If you can get 1320ish ac and tend to get alot of agro and tank alot then its certainly an appealing option.  (This info comes off a warriors board btw.)<br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessage?topicID=1243.topic">pub14.ezboard.com/ftheste...1243.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>Combat agility has real promise.  Check the Library, Kendrick's Comments on Kunarkian Rogues.  Pay attention to the part about the rogues having increased damage avoidance.  If thats true (dunno if it is or isnt) then CA has great potential at adding to our defense since its percentage based off an already large number.  However, like CS, it is only useful in defensive melee combat.<br><br>Durability is an odd duck.  Unlike CA we wont see as much improvement as a warrior or pal/sk.  It is however the only one, aside from perhaps more regen, that will protect you from AEs by giving you more of a hp buffer.  Consider your encounters and what gear you already have.  With an ac cap pretty much agreed upon it may come down to sheep hp being the only thing you can really improve upon.  If so then this one is an appealing choice.<br><br>Finishing blow is useful however the description implies that it only has a chance of going off on a crit so it might be worth it to max CF first.<br><br>I will say this, there is definately a difference between CF 1 and CF 3.  You will do more damage with CF3.  Plus the huge backstabs are just cool. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Tobie Baine<br>Assassin<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showNextMessage?topicID=23012.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23012.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.emailToFriend?topicID=23012.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/ima